* Near '''Shōjōin''', there is '''{{ill|Keiunji (Arakawa)|ja|啓運寺|12=draft}}''', which enshrines '''Bishamonten'''. Many pilgrims '''pass by this temple''', but it is '''not part of the official Yanaka Seven Lucky Gods route'''. * The composition of the '''Yanaka Seven Lucky Gods''' was '''not fixed during the Edo period'''. In the past: ** '''Ebisu''' was enshrined at '''Kanda Myōjin''' or '''Shimizu Kannon-dō'''. ** '''Daikokuten''' was at '''Kyōōji'''. ** '''Bishamonten''' was at '''Hon-dōji in Yanaka'''. ** '''Benzaiten''' was at '''Yōsenji in Kitamachi'''.
