During the pilgrimage period, visitors can purchase '''woodblock-printed stamp sheets''' to collect {{ill|Shuin|ja|朱印|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (temple stamps). Outside this period, although temple grounds are generally accessible, the '''Seven Lucky Gods statues may not be visible''', as '''halls may be closed'''.
== Overview ==
* '''Area:''' {{ill|Taitō, Tokyo|ja|台東区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Arakawa, Tokyo|ja|荒川区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kita, Tokyo|ja|北区|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * '''Distance:''' Approx. 5.5 km * '''Time required:''' Approx. 2 hours * '''Pilgrimage period:''' January 1 – January 10 (until 2009, January 1 – January 15) / 9:00 – 17:00 * '''Temple stamps (Goshuin):''' ** '''Paper or colored paper:''' ¥200 ** '''Goshuin book (shuinchō):''' ¥300 ** '''Stamp sheet:''' ¥1,000, made of '''Japanese paper (not thick colored paper)''', unique to '''Yanaka Seven Lucky Gods''' (approx. '''A3 size'''). ** In '''recent years''', some temples have increased the goshuin fee to '''¥500''' (others may follow suit). ** Although '''not officially announced''', '''if visitors bring a blank thick-paper sheet''', it is possible to collect '''goshuin''' on it (inquire at each temple).
== Yanaka Seven Lucky Gods List ==
* '''{{ill|Kaneiji|ja|寛永寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' – '''Benzaiten''' (弁才天) at '''Benten-dō''' (不忍池弁天堂) – {{ill|Uenosakuragi, Taitō|ja|上野桜木, 台東区|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * '''{{ill|Gokokuin (Taitō)|ja|護国院|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' (sub-temple of Kaneiji) – '''Daikokuten''' (大黒天) – {{ill|Ueno Park|ja|上野恩賜公園, 台東区|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * '''{{ill|Tennōji (Taitō)|ja|天王寺 (台東区)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' – '''Bishamonten''' (毘沙門天) – {{ill|Yanaka, Taitō|ja|谷中, 台東区|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * '''{{ill|Chōanji (Taitō)|ja|長安寺 (台東区)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' – '''Jurojin''' (寿老人) – Yanaka, Taitō * '''{{ill|Shōjōin (Arakawa)|ja|修性院|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' – '''Hotei''' (布袋) – {{ill|Nishinippori, Arakawa|ja|西日暮里, 荒川区|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * '''{{ill|Seiunji (Arakawa)|ja|青雲寺 (荒川区)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' – '''Ebisu''' (恵比須) – Nishinippori, Arakawa * '''{{ill|Tōkakuji (Tokyo)|ja|東覚寺 (東京都北区)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' – '''Fukurokuju''' (福禄寿) – {{ill|Tabata, Kita, Tokyo|ja|田端, 北区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* Near '''Shōjōin''', there is '''{{ill|Keiunji (Arakawa)|ja|啓運寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''', which enshrines '''Bishamonten'''. Many pilgrims '''pass by this temple''', but it is '''not part of the official Yanaka Seven Lucky Gods route'''. * The composition of the '''Yanaka Seven Lucky Gods''' was '''not fixed during the Edo period'''. In the past: ** '''Ebisu''' was enshrined at '''Kanda Myōjin''' or '''Shimizu Kannon-dō'''. ** '''Daikokuten''' was at '''Kyōōji'''. ** '''Bishamonten''' was at '''Hon-dōji in Yanaka'''. ** '''Benzaiten''' was at '''Yōsenji in Kitamachi'''.
